= extend("/slm/layouts/default")

- title = "Crisis Support | Programs | Mental Health for All"

= content("main")
  div class="js-parallax"
    header class="c-hero c-hero--large c-hero--long-text js-parallax-content bg-toddler--primary"
      div class="o-container js-parallax-text"
        h1 class="c-hero__title c-hero__title--long"
          | Crisis Support

        p class="c-hero__tagline desktop:w-6/12"
          | ThriveNYC | NYC Well

        p class="c-hero__tags"
          a href="#" class="button--pill" Crisis Support

  article class="o-container u-bottom-spacing-small js-sticky-container desktop:flex"
    div class="o-article-sidebar desktop:w-sidebar"
      div class="o-content-container--compact u-shift-up"
        ol class="c-nav-list js-sticky js-section-set o-sticky-nav" style=("width: 357px;")
          li class="c-nav-list__item"
            a class="scroll js-section c-nav-list__link bg-toddler--secondary" data-section="section-eligibility" href="#section-eligibility"
              | What to know
              svg class="icon--caret" aria-hidden="true"
                use xlink:href="#icon-caret-right"
          li class="c-nav-list__item"
            a class="scroll js-section c-nav-list__link bg-toddler--secondary" data-section="section-call-to-action" href="#section-call-to-action"
              | How to get Help?
              svg class="icon--caret" aria-hidden="true"
                use xlink:href="#icon-caret-right"
          li class="c-nav-list__item"
            a class="scroll js-section c-nav-list__link bg-toddler--secondary" data-section="section-help" href="#section-help"
              | Other ways to get help
              svg class="icon--caret" aria-hidden="true"
                use xlink:href="#icon-caret-right"
    div class="o-article js-sticky-article desktop:w-article m-auto"
      div class="o-content-container--compact"
        section id="section-eligibility" class="o-content-container--text s-wysiwyg u-top-spacing u-bottom-spacing-small" tabindex="-1"
          h2 id="section-call-to-action" tabindex="-1"  Support during a crisis
          p In New York City, support is always available in the most difficult of moments. Talk to an NYC Well counselor; itâ€™s free, confidential, and available 24/7. Additionally, mobile crisis teams staffed by health professionals, can offer support to an individual in crisis in their home.
          p Mobile crisis teams offer a range of services, including:
          .list-unordered--check
            ul
              li Assessment
              li Crisis intervention
              li Supportive counseling
              li Information and referrals, including to community-based mental health services
          p Request help from a mobile crisis team if a family member, friend, or acquaintance is experiencing (or at risk of) a psychological crisis. You can also request a team for yourself.

        section class="o-content-container--text s-wysiwyg u-bottom-spacing-small" data-id="section-call-to-action"
          h2 id="section-call-to-action" tabindex="-1"  How to get Help?
          .layout--three-columns.bg-color-gray-light.text-center
            div class='c-card m-0 pr-6 flex'
              h3 class='c-card__subtitle'
                strong
                  == 'Talk to a counselor or request a mobile crisis team'

              div class="c-card__subtitle"
                p
                  strong
                    == "1-888-NYC-WELL (1-888-692-9355)"
                p
                  == "Available 24 hours a day, 7 days a week"

          .layout--three-columns.bg-color-gray-light.text-center
            div class='c-card m-0 pr-6 flex'
              h3 class='c-card__subtitle'
                strong
                  == 'Text a counselor'

              div class="c-card__subtitle"
                p
                  strong
                    == "Text 'WELL' to 65173"

          .layout--three-columns.bg-color-gray-light.text-center
             div class='c-card m-0 pr-6 flex'
              h3 class='c-card__subtitle'
                strong
                  == 'Chat with a counselor online'

              div class="c-card__subtitle"
                p
                  strong
                    == "Go to nyc.gov/nycwell"
        section id="section-eligibility" class="o-content-container--text s-wysiwyg u-bottom-spacing-small" tabindex="-1"
          h2 Other ways to get help
          p Visit NYC Well to learn more about who to call during a crisis.Learn more about the City's services for people in crisis and how to request support here: https://www1.nyc.gov/site/doh/health/health-topics/crisis-emergency-services-mobile-crisis-teams.page


  div class="mobile:pt-5 tablet:pt-12 pb-6"
    a href="#main" class="back-to-top bg-color-blue-light hover:bg-color-blue no-underline" id="myBtn" data-js="back-to-top" title="Back To Top"
      | Back To Top

= content("scripts")
